[blockquote 
	" Famtasia is no longer allowed for submissions on this site.
	$LF
]blockquote
[div class=p 
	"Famtasia is a Windows-only NES emulator. It is deprecated and no longer under development.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Historically, Famtasia is important as it was the first emulator supported by this site, and the emulator that 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/Morimoto 
		"Morimoto
	]a
	" used for his 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Super Mario Bros. 3 TAS|href=/668M)
	". Despite its shortcomings, it was widely accepted until FCE Ultra was introduced.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Shortcomings 
	" Shortcomings
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Famtasia has various shortcomings, some of which include the following:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" It is lacking in emulation quality.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" It assumes that all games use NTSC (60 fps).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" The source code has been lost.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" It is difficult to record AVI.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" No frame advance and no input or frame count display.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" No bulletproof rerecording. Bulletproof rerecording is a safety measure that protects movies from loading of previous savestates.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/blip 
		"blip
	]a
	" improved Famtasia using various patches.
	$LF
]div
[blockquote 
	" 
	[a href=http://bisqwit.iki.fi/utils/famtasiapatch.php rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Famtasia (patch machine)
	]a
	$LF
]blockquote
[blockquote 
	" 
	[a href=https://web.archive.org/web/20090220225932/http://famtasia.at.infoseek.co.jp/term.html rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Official homepage of Famtasia
	]a
	$LF
]blockquote
[h4 id=FamtasiaRomLoadingError 
	" Famtasia ROM Loading Error
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	[img class=embedleft mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/EmulatorResources/Famtasia/romfail.png 
	]img
	$LF
	"When Famtasia says "This file is maybe illegal image" as shown in the image at left and refuses to load your ROM, it's because the ROM is garbled.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The most common reason for this is the "DiskDude!" advertisement tag in the ROM header.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The .NES file format specification states that those bytes should be zero, so Famtasia expects them to be. You can zero those 9 bytes with a hex editor if this is the problem for you.
	$LF
]div
